# Documentation & Releases

## README sections

Installation, Configuration, Usage, Changelog, License, Support. Keep user-facing; reference issues as `fixes #XX`.

## Changelog format

```markdown
<!--
  ### **WORK IN PROGRESS**
-->

### **WORK IN PROGRESS**

- (skvarel) Modified scan path picker to show more adapter folders and subfolders

### 0.1.5 (2026-05-29)
- (skvarel) Added automatic scan interval configuration
- (skvarel) Fixed repo checker issue
```

### User-facing content only

Changelog entries appear in the ioBroker update dialog. Document **user-relevant changes only** — skip minor internal fixes, log tweaks, or layout details unless users would notice.

### Consistent verb prefixes

Each line starts with `(skvarel)` followed by a **past-tense English verb**:

- **Added** — new feature, option, state, tab
- **Fixed** — bug fix users would notice
- **Modified** — changed existing behavior or UI
- **Replaced** — swapped one approach for another
- **Removed** — dropped feature or option

Never use bold type tags in changelog lines (breaks io-package news translation).

## Workflow

- **During development:** new entries **only** under `### **WORK IN PROGRESS**`
- **Never edit released version blocks** (e.g. `### 0.2.0`) — only WIP until release
- **Release:** `npm run release-patch|minor|major` — script sets version, moves WIP to version block, older entries to `CHANGELOG_OLD.md`
- **Never** edit `CHANGELOG_OLD.md` manually

## io-package.json

- Keep `common.version` in sync with `package.json`
- Add multilingual `common.news` entries on release (release-script handles this)
- New config options: add to `native` with defaults

## CI/CD

- `ioBroker/testing-action-check@v1` — lint + package check (lint-first)
- `ioBroker/testing-action-adapter@v1` — adapter tests (Node 22.x, 24.x; ubuntu, windows, macos)
- `ioBroker/testing-action-deploy@v1` — npm deploy on version tags
